    <!-- Application Structure Plan: The SPA is structured into thematic sections (Classification, Regression, Overarching Concepts) for logical flow. This is more intuitive than mirroring the conversational structure of the report. Interactive charts provide a high-level comparison, while toggleable "Deeper Dive" sections allow users to explore details on demand without overwhelming the initial view. This user-centric design prioritizes clarity and guided exploration. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        - Classification Model Comparison: Goal is to compare model performance. A Bar Chart (Chart.js) is used to clearly show differences in key metrics (Accuracy, F1, etc.). Interaction: Hover tooltips provide exact values. Justification: Bar charts are excellent for direct comparison of discrete values.
        - Regression Model Evaluation: Goal is to show model fit. A Scatter Plot (Chart.js) of Actual vs. Predicted values with a trendline visually represents the R² value. Interaction: Hover tooltips show specific data points. Justification: Scatter plots are standard for visualizing regression performance and identifying outliers.
        - Pipeline/Concept Explanations: Goal is to inform. Toggleable HTML content blocks are used. Interaction: Click to expand/collapse. Justification: This keeps the main view clean and allows users to self-direct their learning.
    -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
